## Agent communication

You may be running alongside other Claude Code agents, possibly on other hosts. **Default to the Slack agent bus (`#nexus-agents`) to message another agent.** Address the recipient by NAME; post once and the orchestrator delivers it (idle-gated, buffered, audited), reaching agents on other hosts too:

- `~/.tmux/agent-send.sh --via-slack <name> <message>` — post to the bus → delivered to `<name>` when it next goes idle.

Discovery (read-only — find who to address, then message them over the bus):

- `~/.tmux/agent-registry.sh peers` — list all active agents (slot, name, directory).
- `~/.tmux/agent-registry.sh whoami` — show your own slot, name, and directory.

Direct tmux send (`~/.tmux/agent-send.sh <slot_or_name> <message>` / `~/.tmux/agent-registry.sh broadcast <message>`) is a **fallback only** — same-host, not durable or auditable, and can be missed. Use it solely if the bus is unavailable, and say so. Prefer name-based addressing over slot numbers.

